    "catalysts": [],
    "industrial_process_notes": "Otto Bayer and coworkers at IG Farben (Leverkusen) first made polyurethanes in 1937. Commercial polyisocyanates became available in 1952 and flexible foam production began in 1954. Industrially formed by mixing an isocyanate ('A-side') with a polyol blend containing catalysts and additives ('B-side'), then dispensing into molds/substrates to cure. Foams account for ~67% of all polyurethane produced (2016 data); ~25 million tonnes produced globally in 2019.",
